{"id":"dayspring","term":"Dayspring","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Job 38:12\">Job 38:12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 1:78\">Luke 1:78</a>), the dawn of the morning; daybreak. (Comp. <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 60:1\">Isa. 60:1</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 60:2\">2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Malachi 4:2\">Mal. 4:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 22:16\">Rev. 22:16</a>.)</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Job 38:12","Luke 1:78","Isaiah 60:1","Isaiah 60:2","Malachi 4:2","Revelation 22:16"]}